Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.88,0:00:08.11,Default - italics,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Tiger Echo Fist!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.86,0:00:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.21,0:00:12.59,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,There are too many for me to aggro!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.94,0:00:14.30,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,West Wind girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.30,0:00:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long until you can recast your AoE skill?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.82,0:00:19.70,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kawara! And about twenty more seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.38,0:00:21.47,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Shigeru?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.47,0:00:23.12,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Not much different.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.47,0:00:26.45,Default - italics,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,For a PUG, our teamwork's not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.84,0:00:27.63,Default - italics,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.17,0:00:29.70,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,There are just too many.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.40,0:00:34.15,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We need to hold out until the \Nnew kids reach the safe zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.43,0:00:37.97,Default,GirL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, or we won't be able to face the master!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.41,0:02:17.13,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They just keep coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.13,0:02:20.04,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,This is the sixth encounter. \NWhat the hell is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.48,0:02:24.70,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The encounter rate for goblins in \Nthis area shouldn't be this high.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.25,0:02:37.21,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1611,1)}Return of the Goblin King
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.55,0:02:36.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Return of the Goblin King.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.94,0:02:43.90,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's in quite a hurry, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.07,0:02:47.85,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.27,0:02:49.56,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The goblins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.62,0:02:54.86,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,An army of at least a few thousand goblins
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.86,0:02:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is on the move just beyond the next ridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.56,0:02:58.63,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That many?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.98,0:03:01.20,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Any news from the group at the coast?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.58,0:03:06.69,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I can't reach Marielle or Shouryuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.63,0:03:09.27,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That was stupid of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.60,0:03:12.86,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't add the rest to my Friend List.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.86,0:03:14.46,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Nor did I.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.88,0:03:18.16,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I can't reach the other members of \Nthe Black Sword Knights, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.16,0:03:20.13,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.70,0:03:23.47,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What did that goblin army look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.23,0:03:28.35,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,The ones I saw in the valley \Nwere a major raiding force.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.27,0:03:33.06,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen an army that size.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.18,0:03:38.98,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I also saw hobgoblins, trolls, \Nand even demon beasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.32,0:03:42.33,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,They seemed to be heading west-southwest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.33,0:03:44.83,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't tell you any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.27,0:03:49.79,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,So the groups we fought \Nmust have been scouts, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.04,0:03:51.81,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A huge army on the march...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.32,0:03:56.01,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Over that mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.45,0:04:01.27,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,We have the whole Crescent Moon \NAlliance on our Friend Lists...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.66,0:04:02.62,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.62,0:04:03.44,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.03,0:04:06.68,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Can you contact them and ask what's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.27,0:04:10.10,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let Shiro know first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.09,0:04:13.00,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.58,0:04:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep me informed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.60,0:04:17.73,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I'm on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.48,0:04:19.53,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.14,0:04:24.39,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,A mass of blue goblins from the coast?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.11,0:04:26.54,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Sahuagin?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.91,0:04:29.49,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Those monsters live farther south...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:31.00,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.38,0:04:33.66,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's a coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.66,0:04:35.25,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.25,0:04:40.00,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,So all the adventurers at the coast \Nare heading back to the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.55,0:04:43.38,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do, Naotsugu?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.02,0:04:49.34,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,If it comes down to it, we could all \Nuse a return spell to go back...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.78,0:04:54.39,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,If we do that, it'll take us several days \Nto come back here, to Zantleaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.83,0:04:57.16,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Then that's our last resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.17,0:05:00.82,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Marie's in charge of the camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.22,0:05:03.31,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,We'll meet up with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.67,0:05:06.72,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.72,0:05:07.57,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.39,0:05:12.36,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for responding to \Nmy sudden call, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.82,0:05:16.10,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,This is Shiroe, of Log Horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.01,0:05:21.02,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,As the Round Table members are \Ncurrently separated from one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.02,0:05:25.00,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I've taken the irregular step of \Nconvening a telepathic conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.62,0:05:27.29,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I realize it's a bit bothersome,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.29,0:05:30.74,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,but I've designated one person in \Neach of your locations to be a relay,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.35,0:05:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we can have this conversation in \Nas near to real time as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.40,0:05:38.85,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,In the future, I plan to \Nfurther develop this network.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.64,0:05:41.58,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,First, to brief everyone on the situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.05,0:05:45.38,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,This morning, on the Zantleaf Peninsula,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.38,0:05:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,attacks by multiple races of \Ndemi-humans were confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:53.12,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,At the coasts, a minimum of \Nseveral hundred sahuagin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.70,0:05:57.62,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,In the forest, a huge raiding force \Nprimarily composed of goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.20,0:05:59.88,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,There are at least
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.46,0:06:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ten thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.23,0:06:03.28,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,Ten thousand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.08,0:06:08.71,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I believe there to be even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.22,0:06:12.22,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro, do you have any idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.59,0:06:15.35,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,...what the reason for this invasion is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.68,0:06:17.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I believe the driving force behind this invasion
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.56,0:06:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is the "Goblin King's Return."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:22.97,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The "Goblin King's Return"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.69,0:06:27.43,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,In the game, that event occurred regularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.43,0:06:28.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.04,0:06:34.24,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The goblin castle, Seventh Fall, lies deep \Nwithin the forests of the Ouu territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.47,0:06:39.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Twice a year, the Goblin King is crowned there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.68,0:06:44.38,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Before that happens, players are \Ngiven a week to slay him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.90,0:06:49.01,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If they defeat the king before the coronation, \Nthey can acquire rare items.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.83,0:06:52.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Since these items were very powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.46,0:06:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it was an easy event for regular players,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.63,0:06:57.83,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,it was one of the game's most popular events.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.51,0:07:04.52,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,The chief of the area's most powerful clan \Nbecomes the Goblin King.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.04,0:07:10.04,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, by attacking goblin \Nbases around the Ouu area,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.04,0:07:15.03,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,you could weaken them, \Nthus weakening the Goblin King.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.48,0:07:17.29,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And that event had an element
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.29,0:07:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that was nearly forgotten because \Nit almost never happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.52,0:07:27.48,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, if you failed to defeat \Nthe Goblin King during that week,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.48,0:07:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the king was crowned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.79,0:07:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This unified the surrounding clans,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.83,0:07:35.61,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,making the goblins several times more \Nnumerous than they'd previously been.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.03,0:07:38.31,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.65,0:07:40.15,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.15,0:07:40.93,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.26,0:07:42.47,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Then that's it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.47,0:07:43.68,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Since the Apocalypse,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.68,0:07:47.61,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,we've been so busy trying to make \Nthis world livable for ourselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.17,0:07:51.84,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,And we've been so preoccupied \Nwith raising our levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.84,0:07:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we haven't taken any quests from \Nthe People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.99,0:07:57.58,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the result...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.12,0:08:02.83,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean the goblins are \Nat their full strength, Shiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.25,0:08:06.71,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We should assume the Goblin King, his guards,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.10,0:08:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and his armies are stronger than \Nwe've ever seen them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.89,0:08:16.74,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,My bigger concern is how large the \Nsix clans that were united are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.87,0:08:19.84,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,The ones at the camp couldn't do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.84,0:08:22.13,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,but if the Akihabara adventurers banded together,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.13,0:08:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we could wipe them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.46,0:08:26.73,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is the Eastal lords.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.29,0:08:30.44,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, they aren't strong \Nenough to handle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.70,0:08:32.36,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,As if I care!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.86,0:08:35.50,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,They haven't asked us for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.50,0:08:39.22,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,When this was a game, \Nthere was that overpowered army.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.22,0:08:40.95,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Um, it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.70,0:08:43.21,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The Knights of Izumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.48,0:08:44.39,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.67,0:08:49.61,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Heroes born from the People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.02,0:08:52.96,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Stronger even than adventurers...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.96,0:08:55.04,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The ultimate weapon of the humanoid races.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.04,0:08:58.06,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,There are said to be thirteen bands \Nof knights around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.06,0:09:02.22,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,They've always been involved in battles \Nthat determined the world's fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.61,0:09:06.83,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The Knights of Izumo are something like \Nguardians of the Yamato Islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.83,0:09:08.73,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We can rest easy, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.07,0:09:12.74,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But as of now, no one is sure if they really exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.14,0:09:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.18,0:09:16.03,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,You get your news quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.58,0:09:19.87,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, a large battle is unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.60,0:09:23.12,Default,Kr,0000,0000,0000,,At least some people will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.46,0:09:27.62,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We can come back to life, \Nbut the People of the Land...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.31,0:09:31.28,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.49,0:09:34.46,Default,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,Princess? Princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.96,0:09:36.63,Default,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Lenessia?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:40.14,Default,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,He's not here today, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.13,0:09:42.64,Default,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,Crusty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.94,0:09:43.89,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.34,0:09:47.03,Default,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, you've been breakfasting \Ntogether frequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.46,0:09:50.22,Default,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,I would expect him to show up around this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.31,0:09:55.43,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.43,0:09:57.49,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Lenessia, remain calm and listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.73,0:10:02.90,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,A huge goblin army is approaching Maihama.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.90,0:10:04.20,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Ten thousand of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.51,0:10:05.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Ten thousand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.41,0:10:10.17,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,In a few days, they're likely to \Nnumber several times that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.49,0:10:11.91,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,It's the worst disaster imaginable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.91,0:10:14.42,Default,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,There are thirty thousand people in Maihama.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.42,0:10:17.63,Default,Maid,0000,0000,0000,,At most, there are two thousand guards!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.36,0:10:21.39,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm returning to Maihama immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.62,0:10:22.89,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.22,0:10:26.06,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,No, you will remain in the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.06,0:10:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.24,0:10:29.14,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,My father will, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.37,0:10:30.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.95,0:10:34.08,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,This reaches beyond our city of Maihama.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.87,0:10:38.72,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,All the lords must come together \Nat this conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.72,0:10:43.53,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,As high lord, my father has to \Nremain here, at the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.86,0:10:47.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And you want me to help him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.57,0:10:48.54,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.70,0:10:54.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.52,0:11:04.47,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, everyone's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.90,0:11:07.95,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we have curry tonight? Curry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.95,0:11:08.88,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.84,0:11:10.78,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Marie!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.24,0:11:12.16,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Naotsugu...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.16,0:11:13.44,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Marielle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.44,0:11:15.61,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Serara, you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.22,0:11:17.61,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.91,0:11:19.95,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You're still a little kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.95,0:11:21.07,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.07,0:11:23.58,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Naotsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.34,0:11:26.12,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,For what happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.36,0:11:28.01,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.01,0:11:30.12,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.47,0:11:35.63,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, every adventurer is \Nresponsible for this disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.74,0:11:37.93,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.89,0:11:40.82,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't like you to overthink things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.26,0:11:43.68,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to Shiro. He'll handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.17,0:11:47.79,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,He'll come up with a way out of this, \Neven if it means cheating a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.28,0:11:51.44,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,She smiled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.91,0:11:54.50,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,It's getting cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.50,0:11:56.84,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,You should change.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.38,0:11:58.29,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.29,0:12:00.32,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Give me a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.85,0:12:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.06,0:12:09.46,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.37,0:12:14.40,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Put out the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.40,0:12:15.35,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.35,0:12:16.09,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.48,0:12:18.34,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Torches...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.48,0:12:26.12,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,A goblin army?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.12,0:12:26.97,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.90,0:12:31.64,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Someone, bring me a map!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.64,0:12:34.65,SignA,N,0000,0000,0000,,Gobs                                     Fish
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.12,0:12:36.51,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,How does it look?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.05,0:12:40.71,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,This is a bit of a problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.71,0:12:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.11,0:12:46.80,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Well, not so much for us, perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.80,0:12:48.12,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to sugarcoat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.12,0:12:49.66,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Out with it, Mr. Retiree.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.09,0:12:55.46,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the goblins intend \Nto attack the town of Choushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.00,0:13:00.71,SignA,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(696,1)\an7}Fish
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.00,0:13:00.71,SignA,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(696,1)\an4}Gobs
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.14,0:13:04.93,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, that isn't the giant \Narmy I saw this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:07.60,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,It's a medium-sized division.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.60,0:13:11.02,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The main force is way up north...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.35,0:13:12.97,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.97,0:13:15.23,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's a raiding force.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.68,0:13:19.73,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, they plan to take \Nfood from the town of Choushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.26,0:13:23.98,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Choushi has no walls...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.98,0:13:24.99,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.27,0:13:28.79,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,If we leave them, they won't last until morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.35,0:13:32.49,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We can't return to Akihabara \Nwithout doing anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.82,0:13:34.84,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We should go to Choushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.79,0:13:36.96,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:40.50,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what we can do, \Nbut it's better than staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.71,0:13:41.92,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.30,0:13:43.42,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Isuzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.77,0:13:45.42,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't training...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.42,0:13:48.43,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We don't even know how strong they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.72,0:13:51.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm well aware of that, Miss Isuzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.86,0:13:55.43,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But the people in the town don't \Neven know the goblins are coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.21,0:14:03.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to do nothing, \Neven knowing all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.50,0:14:06.82,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Let's leave this stuff to the adults, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.82,0:14:08.99,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying we're kids?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.99,0:14:10.47,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.47,0:14:13.05,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We've already grown plenty strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.05,0:14:14.89,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.89,0:14:17.54,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I agree with Rundel Haus.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.89,0:14:21.00,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Though, I don't think it's about \Nhow much stronger we are...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.23,0:14:22.57,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Minori...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.57,0:14:25.76,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Please let us go to Choushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:33.01,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how big their army is, \Ntheir numbers don't pose much threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.69,0:14:36.84,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,With our fifteen hundred, \Nwe could destroy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.84,0:14:42.02,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,During that last conference, \NIsaac said that we haven't been asked to,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.02,0:14:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we have no reason to help...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.43,0:14:47.10,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,If he's going to do it, he needs a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.10,0:14:49.49,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.84,0:14:52.53,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro didn't seem like himself, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.86,0:14:57.05,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, he'd make a quick decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.16,0:15:01.67,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Just in case, I've asked Soujirou to join us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:05.24,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If the palace is attacked, he'll help.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.24,0:15:07.92,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,All the representatives of the nobles are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.18,0:15:10.17,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We can't leave it undefended.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.48,0:15:13.41,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,The West Wind Brigade is small but powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.92,0:15:16.65,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,They won't alarm the nobles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.03,0:15:18.18,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.49,0:15:22.94,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The nobles haven't said anything, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.94,0:15:26.44,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they're talking on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.62,0:15:28.98,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Without us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.98,0:15:30.20,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.51,0:15:33.45,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Then should we go to them, strategist?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.30,0:15:37.95,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Before that, there's something \NI need to tell you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.24,0:15:39.20,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.60,0:15:42.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's about death in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.43,0:15:46.88,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If we die, we revive at the Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.43,0:15:50.58,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If we pay an EXP penalty, our bodies come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.48,0:15:53.53,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it was in {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.53,0:15:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we made the mistake of believing \Nit would be the same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.22,0:15:59.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,From the information I've gained,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.43,0:16:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,death carries risks in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.92,0:16:06.58,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll spare you the details,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.12,0:16:10.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems that each death steals \Na small portion of your memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.69,0:16:11.49,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.64,0:16:12.61,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Our memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.94,0:16:17.06,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,How much do we lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.48,0:16:18.54,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.54,0:16:20.52,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Which memories do we lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.52,0:16:21.41,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:23.01,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.01,0:16:24.16,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.55,0:16:25.92,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.36,0:16:30.60,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But judging from the hypotheses \NI've gathered, it seems to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.08,0:16:34.02,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.53,0:16:38.93,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's why I'm missing some of my memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.48,0:16:40.53,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I'm convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.64,0:16:44.50,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,D.D.D. is a combat guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.06,0:16:47.32,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Before the restoration of Akihabara,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.32,0:16:51.69,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,we underwent difficult combat training \Nto adapt to this world's fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.29,0:16:54.60,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I died a few times, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.13,0:16:57.01,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, I wouldn't think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.01,0:16:59.70,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,but it does seem that some memories were lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.07,0:17:01.20,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.44,0:17:02.83,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.23,0:17:05.18,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Which memories, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.66,0:17:06.83,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,How many of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.24,0:17:08.95,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't say for certain,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.95,0:17:13.09,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems most of them were \Nmemories of the world I came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.36,0:17:19.59,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I've died twice since the Apocalypse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.08,0:17:23.54,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to say exactly which \Nmemories are missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.15,0:17:26.69,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Because you forget that you forgot, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.46,0:17:30.77,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,My memory is better than that of most,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.77,0:17:34.66,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,but I can't recall the name or appearance \Nof the cat I'm sure I once had.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.66,0:17:36.70,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,This is likely due to my deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.40,0:17:39.78,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,However, while I can only speak for myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.78,0:17:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a few deaths don't seem to be enough \Nto cause any real inconvenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.18,0:17:49.71,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Even a few dozen would be unlikely \Nto cause any difficulty in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.06,0:17:54.98,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But even so... You lose your memories \Nof the old world, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.98,0:17:56.72,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's harsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.02,0:17:59.72,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's not something to fret over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.68,0:18:02.64,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,You simply need to avoid dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.01,0:18:06.49,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,And failing to act, for fear of the risk,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.49,0:18:09.35,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,is no different than a living death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.86,0:18:11.48,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what world you're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.82,0:18:17.49,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The risk is too great!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:19.57,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.57,0:18:21.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If you fear risk, how can you be an adventurer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.77,0:18:23.49,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.77,0:18:27.62,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The lords' conference will hash out the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.62,0:18:30.02,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Acting on our own right now isn't a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.50,0:18:32.00,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Especially with the new kids here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.23,0:18:36.33,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,This will affect relations between the \Nadventurers and People of the Land
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.33,0:18:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for a long time to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.86,0:18:41.51,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And we have no ostensible reason to save them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.75,0:18:43.78,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,When you consider the big picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.78,0:18:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,acting based on emotion isn't wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.95,0:18:47.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.05,0:18:51.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of this. I'll go on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.49,0:18:53.51,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! You can't go alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.51,0:18:54.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.42,0:18:56.41,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We're a party, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.58,0:19:01.58,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If we aren't all in this together, \Nbut we go, we'll just get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.58,0:19:03.28,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Like we did at the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.54,0:19:05.37,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But if something isn't done...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:10.76,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, make us the advance party to Choushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.69,0:19:14.38,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,An advance party?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.38,0:19:16.80,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A brilliant idea, Miss Minori.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.24,0:19:20.33,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,We can at least help them evacuate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.33,0:19:24.65,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,No... Saying that was the only \Nway to get them to agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.14,0:19:26.18,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.59,0:19:29.69,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I think we should protect that city.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.71,0:19:32.44,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.94,0:19:34.33,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,No one's asked us to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.33,0:19:35.54,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,No one will reward us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.54,0:19:37.34,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't have anything to do with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.34,0:19:38.56,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't want to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.23,0:19:42.18,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,There are many reasons not to help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.98,0:19:46.32,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But there isn't any reason we can't, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.32,0:19:47.69,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.55,0:19:49.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.04,0:20:02.46,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.46,0:20:03.43,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We're too late?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.67,0:20:05.83,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Goblins did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.83,0:20:07.03,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Is anyone here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.05,0:20:27.79,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.07,0:20:30.25,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll assist you, Mister Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.77,0:20:32.21,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,Flash Needle!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.26,0:20:34.79,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Head Splitter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.66,0:20:42.21,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.76,0:20:45.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Is helping them without one wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.66,0:20:49.74,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to help someone, isn't that enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.86,0:20:53.24,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We're adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.79,0:20:54.61,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.02,0:20:58.52,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If we run away, then I don't know \Nwhy we became adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.26,0:21:03.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We can't just boldly march home to \NAkihabara without saving the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.64,0:21:06.12,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But how are we supposed to protect them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.12,0:21:08.87,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That town has no walls, and there are so many!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.04,0:21:10.55,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.55,0:21:12.82,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We're back to that again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.82,0:21:14.41,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Put some thought into it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.41,0:21:16.42,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I am thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.02,0:21:18.67,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,There is a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.65,0:21:20.84,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.84,0:21:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With our numbers, protecting Choushi \Nfrom the goblins is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.72,0:21:31.56,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,And even if we could, it's pointless \Nif other places are razed like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.19,0:21:33.14,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That's why
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.07,0:21:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we don't protect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.89,0:21:38.40,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,M-Miss Minori, what do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.28,0:21:42.63,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Minori's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.01,0:21:49.91,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,We came to make sure you young kids \Nweren't getting yourselves into trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.30,0:21:51.33,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Nyanta!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.33,0:21:52.41,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Master Naotsugu!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.89,0:21:56.17,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Please give us permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.93,0:21:59.98,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Adventurers are free. \NThey don't need permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.45,0:22:02.99,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,If you've thought for yourself and \Nreached your own decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.99,0:22:05.30,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,you have the freedom to \Nsee that decision through.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.08,0:22:10.82,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,However, Minori, it won't be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.82,0:22:12.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Chief! Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.22,0:22:14.84,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's a man's job to be quiet and let us go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.10,0:22:17.28,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Minori's had an idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.99,0:22:19.72,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.72,0:22:21.77,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,At least let us hear it first...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.07,0:22:24.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Minori's idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.42,0:22:24.99,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.26,0:22:29.21,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We drop the idea of protecting the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.21,0:22:31.44,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Instead, we seize the initiative.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.34,0:22:35.28,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We attack the goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.96,0:24:09.66,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Minori and the rest begin their \Nbattle against the goblin army.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.05,0:24:12.74,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,They have no reason but to protect others.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.74,0:24:14.30,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That is the freedom of an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.54,0:24:16.22,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But freedom requires resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.64,0:24:20.38,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,When a girl breaks out of her \Nshell and makes her decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.38,0:24:22.44,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,her body will rise into the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.69,0:24:30.99,Title,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,A Lazy, Cowardly Princess
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.77,0:24:25.06,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: A Lazy, Cowardly Princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.43,0:24:27.81,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Always look thirty seconds ahead.
